  "prompt": "What are some signs that someone is a n00b at Physics?",
  "response": "Here are some potential signs that someone might be new or inexperienced in physics:\n\n1. Confusing basic concepts like mass, weight, and force\n\n2. Struggling to use scientific notation or unit conversions\n\n3. Not understanding the difference between velocity and acceleration\n\n4. Misusing terms like \"theory\" and \"hypothesis\"\n\n5. Overcomplicating simple problems or not knowing how to break down complex problems\n\n6. Being unable to do basic dimensional analysis\n\n7. Thinking physics is just about memorizing equations rather than understanding principles\n\n8. Difficulty interpreting graphs or experimental data\n\n9. Lack of comfort with mathematical modeling\n\n10. Not knowing how to set up or solve basic mechanics problems\n\n11. Confusion about significant figures and measurement uncertainty\n\n12. Believing physics is purely theoretical with no practical applications\n\nRemember, being a beginner is completely normal and everyone starts somewhere. These are just potential indicators of someone early in their physics learning journey.",
